results.lead_paragraph: If American officials had written the scenario, they could hardly have planned an ending of the moon race more satisfactory to Washington than the one that actually occurred. The contrast between last week's triumphant walk by American astronauts on the moon and the inglorious lunar crash landing of the unmanned Soviet Luna 15 underlined American space superiority if any underlining were needed.
